Appendix D: Memory‑Augmented Architectures

D.1 Differentiable Neural Computers (DNCs)

Definition D.1 (DNC Read/Write). A DNC (Graves et al., 2016) consists of:

· Memory matrix M_t \in \mathbb{R}^{N_m \times D_m},
· Read vectors r_t \in \mathbb{R}^{D_m},
· Write weights w_t \in \Delta^{N_m-1}.

Read: r_t = \sum_{i=1}^{N_m} w_t^i M_t[i,:].

Write: M_t[i,:] = (1 - w_t^i) M_{t-1}[i,:] + w_t^i \mathbf{v}_t, where \mathbf{v}_t is the write vector.

D.2 Memory‑Augmented Transformers (MATs)

Definition D.2 (Cross‑Attention with Memory). For queries Q \in \mathbb{R}^{n \times d_k} and memory keys K_m \in \mathbb{R}^{N_m \times d_k}, values V_m \in \mathbb{R}^{N_m \times d_v},

\text{Attention}(Q, K_m, V_m) = \text{softmax}\left(\frac{Q K_m^T}{\sqrt{d_k}}\right) V_m.

Definition D.3 (Gated Memory Update). The memory update with surprise d_t and threshold \tau is

\alpha_t = \sigma(\text{MLP}_{\text{gate}}(d_t - \tau)), \quad M_t = \alpha_t M_{t-1} + (1 - \alpha_t) \text{Write}(h_t, z_t).

D.3 Variational Memory Gap

Theorem D.1 (Bounded Variational Memory Gap). Let \mathcal{L}_{\text{true}} be the exact ELBO with full memory distribution q(M_t \mid M_{t-1}, \Delta_t) and \mathcal{L}_{\text{approx}} be the approximation using LRU writes. Then

|\mathcal{L}_{\text{true}} - \mathcal{L}_{\text{approx}}| \leq \mathbb{E}_t\left[\log \frac{1}{\pi_{\text{LRU}}(M_t)}\right] \leq \log N_m.

Proof. The gap equals the KL divergence between the true memory posterior and the LRU approximation. The maximum KL is attained when the LRU distribution is uniform over the N_m slots, giving \log N_m. ∎

