Appendix F: Recurrent Neural Network Stability

F.1 Lyapunov Stability for Discrete‑Time Systems

Definition F.1 (Contraction). A discrete‑time system h_{t+1} = F(h_t, u_t) is contracting if there exists \rho \in [0,1) such that for all h, h', u,

\|F(h, u) - F(h', u)\| \leq \rho \|h - h'\|.

Theorem F.1 (GRU Contraction). Assume the GRU parameters satisfy \|W_z\|_2, \|W_r\|_2, \|W_h\|_2 \leq \gamma < 1 and the activation functions have Lipschitz constant 1. Then the GRU update is a contraction with \rho = \gamma + \gamma^2.

Proof. The GRU equations:

\begin{aligned}
z_t &= \sigma_g(W_z x_t + U_z h_{t-1} + b_z), \\
r_t &= \sigma_g(W_r x_t + U_r h_{t-1} + b_r), \\
\tilde{h}_t &= \tanh(W_h x_t + U_h (r_t \odot h_{t-1}) + b_h), \\
h_t &= (1 - z_t) \odot h_{t-1} + z_t \odot \tilde{h}_t.
\end{aligned}

By Lipschitz continuity of \sigma_g and \tanh,

\|z_t - z_t'\| \leq \|U_z\|_2 \|h_{t-1} - h_{t-1}'\| \leq \gamma \|h_{t-1} - h_{t-1}'\|,

\|r_t - r_t'\| \leq \gamma \|h_{t-1} - h_{t-1}'\|.

For the hidden state:

\begin{aligned}
\|h_t - h_t'\| &\leq \|1 - z_t\| \|h_{t-1} - h_{t-1}'\| + \|z_t - z_t'\| \|\tilde{h}_t\| + \|z_t'\| \|\tilde{h}_t - \tilde{h}_t'\| \\
&\leq \gamma \|h_{t-1} - h_{t-1}'\| + \gamma \|h_{t-1} - h_{t-1}'\| B_h + \gamma \|h_{t-1} - h_{t-1}'\|,
\end{aligned}

where we used boundedness of \tilde{h}_t and z_t. Summing gives \rho = \gamma + \gamma^2. ∎

F.2 Boundedness of Hidden State

Theorem F.2 (Bounded Hidden State). Under the contraction assumption and with bounded inputs \|\mathbf{u}_t\| \leq B_u and memory read \|\mathbf{r}_t\| \leq B_r,

\|\mathbf{h}_t\| \leq \rho^t \|\mathbf{h}_0\| + \frac{B_u + B_r}{1 - \rho}.

Proof. Let h_t^* be the fixed point of the map with zero input. Then

\|h_t\| \leq \|h_t - h_t^*\| + \|h_t^*\| \leq \rho^t \|h_0 - h_0^*\| + \sum_{k=0}^{t-1} \rho^k (B_u + B_r).

The geometric series converges to (B_u + B_r)/(1 - \rho). ∎

F.3 Robustness to Perturbations

Corollary F.1 (Robustness to Memory Perturbations). If memory writes introduce bounded perturbations \|\delta_t\| \leq \epsilon, the asymptotic bound becomes

\|\mathbf{h}_t\| \leq \frac{B_u + B_r + \epsilon}{1 - \rho}.

Proof. The perturbation adds at most \epsilon to each step’s bound. Summing the geometric series yields the result. ∎

